{
  "bead_id": "B-18f52ffa",
  "title": "Run scheduler to full quiescence in takt run",
  "agent_type": "planner",
  "description": "Make `takt run` repeatedly call `Scheduler.run_once()` until a cycle dispatches no beads, instead of executing a single cycle and exiting. Adds a `--max-cycles` safety cap, per-cycle telemetry events with `cycle_index`, and per-cycle console progress markers. Eliminates the operator UX problem where beads unblocked mid-cycle (e.g. a tester re-queued after a corrective completes) are silently left pending until a second manual `takt run` invocation.",
